%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22Stop%20thinking%20tenure%20gets%20you%20promotions%20%E2%80%94%20it%20doesn't.%20A%20former%20senior%20leader%20at%20Amazon%20explains%20what%20actually%20works.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221559%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Brandon%20Southern%20headshot%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F647270a8085acb0018fec7c2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221169%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBrandon%20Southern%20is%20the%20former%20head%20of%20analytics%20at%20eBay%2C%20Amazon%2C%20and%20GameStop.%3Cp%3EBrandon%20Southern%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EBrandon%20Southern%20is%20the%20former%20head%20of%20analytics%20at%20eBay%2C%20Amazon%2C%20and%20GameStop.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EHe%20says%20that%20you%20shouldn't%20mistake%20tenure%20for%20value.%20Companies%20won't%20pay%20more%20for%20the%20same%20service.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ETo%20get%20a%20raise%2C%20show%20the%20company%20you've%20significantly%20increased%20your%20skills%20or%20responsibilities.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20former%20senior%20leader%20in%20analytics%20roles%20at%20Amazon%2C%20eBay%2C%20and%20other%20organizations%2C%20I've%20frequently%20witnessed%20employees%20cite%20tenure%20in%20their%20list%20of%20reasons%20for%20deserving%20a%20promotion%20or%20a%20raise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20time%20spent%20in%20a%20specific%20role%20may%20correlate%20with%20commitment%2C%20experience%2C%20or%20knowledge%2C%20it%20doesn't%20necessarily%20correlate%20with%20value%20to%20a%20company.%20To%20get%20a%20raise%20or%20promotion%2C%20you're%20going%20to%20need%20more%20than%20tenure%20%E2%80%94%20you're%20going%20to%20need%20to%20create%20additional%20value%20or%20increase%20your%20scope%20of%20work.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYears%20ago%2C%20I%20was%20working%20at%20a%20large%20tech%20company%2C%20and%20I%20was%20speaking%20with%20a%20coworker.%20This%20person%20had%20been%20with%20the%20company%20for%20six%20years%20and%20he%20was%20frustrated%20about%20never%20being%20promoted.%20He%20stated%20that%20he%20put%20in%20his%20time%2C%20had%20been%20loyal%20to%20the%20company%2C%20watched%20others%20get%20promoted%20after%20only%20a%20few%20years%2C%20and%20said%20he%20deserved%20a%20promotion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20reading%20about%20a%20similar%20situation%20where%20an%20hourly%20retail%20employee%20was%20lamenting%20about%20receiving%20a%202%25%20raise%2C%20even%20though%20she%20had%20been%20an%20employee%20for%20five%20years.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20these%20stories%20have%20in%20common%20is%20that%20both%20individuals%20mistook%20tenure%20for%20value%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20capitalistic%20world%2C%20companies%20care%20about%20getting%20the%20most%20value%20for%20the%20lowest%20cost.%20While%20this%20feels%20brutal%20and%20unfair%20at%20times%20as%20an%20employee%2C%20most%20individuals%20behave%20the%20same%20as%20a%20company%20if%20they%20had%20to%20give%20out%20promotions%20and%20raises.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20if%20you're%20currently%20paying%20%2450%20for%20someone%20to%20mow%20your%20lawn%2C%20you%20wouldn't%20likely%20be%20willing%20to%20pay%20that%20person%20%2460%20to%20do%20the%20same%20job%2C%20simply%20because%20they've%20been%20mowing%20your%20lawn%20for%20the%20last%20three%20months%20or%20the%20last%20three%20years.%20This%20is%20because%20they%20didn't%20provide%20you%20with%20any%20additional%20value.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERegardless%20of%20the%20length%20of%20your%20relationship%20with%20this%20employee%2C%20you%20wouldn't%20want%20to%20pay%20more%20for%20the%20same%20service.%20Neither%20would%20a%20company%2C%20and%20this%20is%20exactly%20how%20they%20are%20thinking%20about%20raises.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EFrom%20a%20company's%20perspective%2C%20there%20two%20main%20considerations%20when%20dealing%20with%20compensation%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20consideration%20is%20about%20the%20value%20that%20is%20being%20generated%20by%20the%20employee%3A%20A%20company%20wants%20to%20get%20the%20best%20value%2C%20not%20necessarily%20the%20lowest%20price.%20They%20could%20find%20an%20entry-level%20salesperson%20with%20no%20experience%20and%20pay%20a%20very%20low%20wage.%C2%A0%20The%20company%20could%20also%20find%20a%20very%20experienced%20salesperson%20who%20would%20likely%20cost%20a%20lot%20more.%20But%20choosing%20between%20the%20two%20options%20requires%20an%20evaluation%20of%20value.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20person%20with%20no%20experience%20costs%20%2440%2C000%2Fyear%2C%20but%20helps%20the%20company%20generate%20%24100%2C000%20in%20sales%20revenue%2C%20the%20company%20is%20getting%20a%202.5x%20return.%20But%20if%20the%20company%20pays%20the%20experienced%20person%20%24200%2C000%2Fyear%20and%20that%20person%20help%20the%20company%20generate%20%241%2C000%2C000%20in%20sales%20revenue%2C%20the%20company%20is%20getting%20a%205x%20return.%20In%20this%20case%2C%20the%20company%20is%20getting%20more%20value%20by%20paying%20more%2C%20but%20paying%20more%20doesn't%20always%20equate%20to%20more%20value.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20we%20fast%20forward%20five%20years%20and%20assume%20that%20the%20person%20making%20%2440%2C000%2Fyear%20asks%20to%20make%20%2450%2C000%2Fyear%2C%20the%20company%20is%20going%20to%20want%20to%20justify%20the%20additional%20cost.%20If%20the%20employee's%20output%20is%205%25%20better%20than%205%20years%20ago%2C%20the%20company%20is%20getting%20more%20value%20as%20they%20are%20making%20%24105%2C000%20instead%20of%20%24100%2C000%20per%20year.%20But%20it's%20costing%20the%20company%20an%20extra%20%2410%2C000%20in%20payroll%20to%20make%20%245%2C000%20in%20revenue.%20This%20is%20a%20poor%20return%20on%20investment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20this%20is%20a%20straight-forward%20example%2C%20calculating%20value%20is%20usually%20very%20difficult%20for%20employees%20who%20are%20not%20salespeople.%20This%20is%20because%20it's%20hard%20to%20connect%20the%20employee's%20efforts%20to%20revenue%20and%20profits%20for%20the%20company.%20For%20many%20positions%2C%20it%20can%20be%20hard%20to%20determine%20if%20an%20experienced%20person%20is%20providing%20more%20value%20than%20a%20non-experienced%20person.%20This%20can%20be%20especially%20true%20with%20unskilled%20labor%20positions.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20hourly%20retail%20employee%20that%20was%20mentioned%20in%20the%20article%20that%20I%20read%2C%20if%20she%20were%20to%20receive%20a%2010%25%20raise%20from%20%2415.00%2Fhr%20to%20%2416.50%2Fhr%2C%20would%20she%20produce%20more%20value%20for%20the%20company%3F%20It's%20difficult%20to%20say%20for%20sure.%20And%20when%20the%20value%20isn't%20easily%20quantifiable%2C%20the%20company%20is%20going%20to%20have%20a%20hard%20time%20justifying%20the%20additional%20labor%20cost.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%C2%A0The%20second%20thing%20that%20the%20company%20must%20consider%20is%20the%20cost%20of%20replacing%20the%20employee%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20not%20giving%20the%20retail%20employee%20a%20raise%20to%20%2416.50%2Fhr%2C%20the%20company%20risks%20the%20employee%20quitting.%20The%20question%20that%20the%20company%20will%20ask%20is%2C%20does%20the%20hire%20salary%20cost%20outweigh%20the%20cost%20of%20hiring%20a%20new%20employee%3F%20If%20the%20company%20can%20hire%20a%20new%20employee%20for%20%2415.00%2Fhr%20and%20they%20don't%20have%20to%20spend%20much%20to%20train%20the%20employee%2C%20it%20might%20be%20worth%20it%20to%20allow%20the%20experience%20employee%20to%20quit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20chances%20are%2C%20even%20if%20the%20cost%20of%20finding%20a%20new%20employee%20would%20exceed%20paying%20the%20current%20employee%20more%2C%20the%20company%20still%20may%20not%20be%20willing%20to%20pay%20more.%20Because%20it%20is%20so%20challenging%20to%20assess%20the%20value%20created%20for%20each%20employee%2C%20the%20company%20may%20run%20into%20a%20risk%20of%20compensation%20inflation.%20This%20could%20occur%20when%20one%20employee%20feels%20that%20they%20deserve%20a%20raise%20based%20on%20tenure%2C%20and%20then%20other%20employees%20request%20a%20raise%20simply%20because%20someone%20else%20got%20a%20raise.%20To%20avoid%20payroll%20inflation%2C%20a%20company%20may%20choose%20to%20allow%20the%20more%20experience%20person%20to%20quit.%C2%A0Also%2C%20the%20company%20is%20used%20to%20dealing%20with%20people%20quitting%20and%20it's%20rarely%20detrimental%20to%20the%20business.%20But%20there%20is%20a%20way%20to%20receive%20a%20raise%2C%20and%20that's%20through%20the%20creation%20of%20value.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EIf%20you%20want%20more%20money%2C%20deliver%20more%20value%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20easiest%20way%20to%20justify%20a%20higher%20salary%20is%20through%20value%20creation%2C%20not%20simply%20by%20staying%20with%20a%20company%20for%20a%20long%20period%20of%20time.%20If%20you're%20looking%20for%20a%20raise%2C%20you'll%20need%20to%20demonstrate%20how%20you've%20provided%20value%2C%20and%20how%20your%20additional%20cost%20(above%20that%20of%20someone%20that%20they%20could%20hire%20today)%20is%20justified.%20And%20if%20you're%20looking%20for%20a%20promotion%2C%20you'll%20have%20to%20demonstrate%20how%20you've%20provided%20a%20significant%20increase%20in%20value%2C%20which%20is%20frequently%20demonstrated%20through%20a%20significant%20increase%20in%20your%20scope%20of%20work%20and%20responsibilities.%20But%20if%20you%20are%20being%20paid%20below%20the%20market%20value%20or%20your%20added%20value%20isn't%20being%20recognized%2C%20it%20may%20be%20time%20to%20find%20an%20organization%20that%20does%20value%20all%20that%20you%20have%20to%20offer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EBrandon%20Southern%20is%20the%20former%20head%20of%20analytics%20at%20eBay%2C%20Amazon%2C%20and%20GameStop.%20He%20also%C2%A0%3Ca%20data-mrf-link%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tiktok.com%2F%40analyticsmentor%3F_t%3D8cgBuY7EINK%26amp%3B_r%3D1%5C%22%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20data-uri%3D%5C%222f2a28156d5c62be58fd47