%20reached%20115%20degrees%20Fahrenheit%2C%20many%20workers%20and%20their%20families%20are%20on%20edge.%20A%2046-year-old%20construction%20worker%20named%20Felipe%20Pascual%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fabc13.com%2Ffort-bend-county-construction-worker-death-felipe-pascual-dies-at-job-site-texas-heat-wave%2F13449783%2F%5C%22%3Edied%20in%20June%20in%20Houston%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20heat%20stroke.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusinesses%20must%20stop%20placing%20profit%20and%20efficiency%20over%20worker%20safety%2C%20said%20Richard%20Gleason%2C%20an%20associate%20teaching%20professor%20on%20workplace%20safety%20and%20occupational%20health%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Washington%2C%20especially%20in%20excessive%20heat.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20has%20got%20to%20be%20some%20extra%20emphasis%20on%20responsibility%20and%20liability%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Occupational%20Safety%20and%20Health%20Administration%2C%20or%20OSHA%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20is%20not%20adding%20much%20punitive%20incentive%20for%20companies%20to%20do%20more%20to%20protect%20workers%20in%20the%20heat.%20According%20to%20federal%20data%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.osha.gov%2Ffatalities%23%26amp%3Bsort%5B%23incSum%5D%3D0-1-1-0%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%20between%202017%20and%202022%2C%20the%20Department%20of%20Labor%20fines%20businesses%20governed%20by%20federal%20OSHA%20regulations%20an%20average%20of%20just%20%248%2C539.98%20if%20an%20employee%20dies%20because%20of%20heat-related%20illness.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeveral%20individual%20penalties%20were%20as%20low%20as%20%242%2C000%2C%20according%20to%20Gleason.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B%242%2C000%20%E2%80%94%20come%20on%2C%20that's%20crazy%2C%26quot%3B%20Gleason%20told%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20that's%20typical%20for%20federal%20OSHA.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.osha.gov%2Fstateplans%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E22%20states%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20have%20state-run%20OSHA%20plans%20that%20govern%20both%20public%20and%20private%20employees.%20State%20OSHA%20plans%20tend%20to%20be%20more%20proactive%20when%20creating%20workplace%20safety%20rules%20and%20have%20more%20inspectors%20who%20can%20monitor%20conditions%2C%20Gleason%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20have%20to%20be%20at%20least%20as%20strict%20as%20%5Bfederal%5D%20OSHA%2C%20but%20they%20can%20be%20better%20and%20safer%2C%26quot%3B%20Gleason%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20incidents%20in%20states%20governed%20by%20federal%20regulations%20%E2%80%94%20such%20as%20an%20unnamed%20employee%20who%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.osha.gov%2Fords%2Fimis%2Festablishment.inspection_detail%3Fid%3D1344643.015%5C%22%3Edied%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20heat%20exhaustion%20while%20working%20with%20a%20coke%20oven%20in%20West%20Virginia%20%E2%80%94%20resulted%20in%20no%20fines%20at%20all.%20The%20lowest%20non-zero%20fine%20came%20out%20of%20Wisconsin%20in%202022%3A%20The%20federal%20office%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.osha.gov%2Fords%2Fimis%2Festablishment.inspection_detail%3Fid%3D1606631.015%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erequired%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20business%20to%20pay%20just%20%241%2C000%20for%20the%20heat-related%20death%20of%2037-year-old%20Thomas%20Linkous%2C%20a%20construction%20worker%20who%20died%20of%20heat%20stroke.%20The%20case%20is%20still%20open%20as%20of%20July%2015%2C%20so%20the%20company%20%E2%80%94%20Farrell%20Quality%20Carpentry%20Inc.%20%E2%80%94%20can%20still%20appeal%20that%20penalty%2C%20meaning%20it%20may%20end%20up%20even%20lower.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20codes%20and%20penalties%20are%20very%20small%2C%26quot%3B%20Gleason%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20average%20fine%20for%20states%20with%20the%20strictest%20state-level%20OSHA%20penalties%20%E2%80%94%20like%20California%2C%20Washington%2C%20and%20Oregon%20%E2%80%94%20tends%20to%20be%20closer%20to%20%2420%2C000%2C%20according%20to%20Gleason.%20But%2C%20Gleason%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BEven%20%2420%2C000%20is%20pretty%20low%20when%20you%20think%20about%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGleason%20also%20noted%20that%20federal%20OSHA%20fines%20for%20worker%20deaths%20are%20significantly%20smaller%20than%20that%20of%20other%20federal%20agencies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20average%20Environmental%20Protection%20Agency%20penalty%20is%2010%20times%20that%20of%20federal%20OSHA%20for%20a%20worker%20that%20dies%2C%26quot%3B%20Gleason%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20pretty%20weird%2C%20if%20you%20ask%20me.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20major%20barrier%20to%20progress%20includes%20the%20slow%20pace%20at%20which%20the%20federal%20OSHA%20office%20can%20change%20its%20policies%2C%20Gleason%20said.%20He%20estimated%20it%20would%20take%2010%20years%20to%20update%20its%20heat-related%20safety%20guidelines%2C%20while%20states%20can%20do%20so%20far%20more%20quickly%20%E2%80%94%20within%20a%20single%20legislative%20session%2C%20even.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20states%20can%20be%20a%20little%20more%20efficient%2C%20they%20can%20change%20their%20own%20rules%2C%26quot%3B%20Gleason%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Department%20of%20Labor%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20ahead%20of%20publication.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-department-of-labor-osha-heat-wave-workers-death-fines-2023-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689509288000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64b19df89751e300192a2d54%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-department-of-labor-osha-heat-wave-workers-death-fines-2023-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Record-breaking%20heat%20in%20the%20United%20States%20is%20a%20threat%20to%20anyone%20who%20works%20outside.%20The%20number%20of%20heat-related%20worker%20deaths%20