2%3A%22bchang%40businessinsider.com%20(Brittany%20Chang)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F9-reasons-royal-caribbean-icon-of-the-seas-shake-industry-2023-7%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I'm%20a%20CEO%20who%20wakes%20up%20at%203%3A45%20a.m.%20without%20an%20alarm%20clock.%20These%2011%20sleep%20hacks%20helped%20me%20become%20a%20better%20leader.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221067%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Michael%20Koch%20headshot.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64b1e29bf9a2590019477015%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMichael%20Koch.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Michael%20Koch%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EMichael%20Koch%20is%20the%20CEO%20and%20cofounder%20of%20HubKonnect%2C%20a%20successful%20AI%20platform.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EKoch%20learned%20the%20value%20of%20sleep%20and%20invested%20in%20optimizing%20his%20bedtime%20and%20productivity.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ENow%20he%20typically%20wakes%20up%20around%203%3A45%20a.m.%20well%20rested%20and%20without%20an%20alarm%20clock%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Michael%20Koch%2C%20a%2045-year-old%20cofounder%20and%20CEO%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhubkonnect.com%2F%23home%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Eof%20HubKonnect%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Cem%3Efrom%20New%20York%20City%2C%20about%20his%20sleep%20hacks.%20It's%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20high%20achiever%20in%20the%20tech%20industry%2C%20where%20I%20focus%20on%20AI%2C%20I've%20created%20my%20own%20protocol%20to%20optimize%20my%20performance%20as%20a%20CEO.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fsleep-cycle%5C%22%3ESleep%20and%20bodily%20recovery%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20two%20non-negotiable%20pillars%20for%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESleep%20is%20the%20time%20we%20heal%20both%20physically%20and%20cognitively.%20So%20I%20started%20blocking%20off%20my%20sleep-time%20just%20like%20it's%20one%20of%20the%20most%20important%20meetings%20of%20the%20day.%20My%20night-time%20schedule%20includes%20these%2011%20sleep%20hacks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E1.%20I%20take%20a%20three-minute%2C%2039-degree%20ice%20bath%20before%20bed%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EGetting%20in%20is%20always%20a%20challenge%20%E2%80%94%20that's%20why%20I%20use%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fmental-health%2Fbox-breathing%5C%22%3ENavy%20box%20breathing%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It's%20four%20breaths%20in%2C%20four%20breaths%20out%2C%20and%20then%20I%20hold%20for%20four%20in%20order%20to%20lower%20my%20breath%20and%20get%20control%20of%20it.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20shock%20to%20the%20system%20every%20time%2C%20but%20I%20remind%20myself%20that%20this%20helps%20prepare%20me%20to%20sleep.%20Even%20if%20I'm%20staying%20in%20a%20hotel%2C%20I'll%20fill%20up%20the%20sink%20with%20water%2C%20add%20ice%2C%20and%20dunk%20my%20face%20in%20the%20cold%20water.%20It's%20almost%20as%20effective%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Ffitness%2Fice-bath%5C%22%3Ea%20full%20body%20ice%20bath%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIce%20baths%20help%20lower%20my%20core%20body%20temperature%20and%20also%20urge%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Ftreatments%2Fmelatonin%5C%22%3Erelease%20of%20melatonin%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20is%20a%20hormone%20that%20helps%20us%20fall%20asleep%20quickly%20and%20remain%20asleep%20until%20we've%20completed%20all%20sleeping%20cycles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E2.%20I%20do%20a%20ten-minute%20red-light%20session%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20have%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fguides%2Fbeauty%2Fred-light-therapy%5C%22%3Ered-light%20therapy%20body%20unit%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20has%20four%20medical-grade%20red-light%20panels%20inside.%20I%20walk%20in%2C%20shut%20the%20door%2C%20drop%20trow%2C%20and%20stand%20in%20front%20of%20the%20light%20butt%20naked%20for%20five%20minutes%20in%20the%20front%20and%20five%20minutes%20at%20the%20back.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Ftucker-carlson-said-red-light-could-boost-testosterone-no-evidence-2022-4%5C%22%3EThe%20red-light%20exposure%3C%2Fa%3E%20increases%20the%20production%20of%20melatonin%20in%20the%20brain.%20This%20is%20how%20I%20balance%20my%20circadian%20rhythm%20and%20feel%20more%20rested%20during%20waking%20hours.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20take%20those%2010%20minutes%20of%20uninterrupted%20time%20to%20clear%20my%20head.%20I%20compartmentalize%20stuff%20into%20buckets%20for%20the%20next%20day%2C%20give%20thanks%20for%20the%20opportunities%20I've%20had%2C%20and%20slow%20down%20my%20breathing%20so%20that%20when%20I%20hit%20the%20pillow%2C%20I'm%20ready%20to%20sleep.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20I%20wear%20blue%20blocker%20glasses%20three%20hours%20before%20bed%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20my%20business%2C%20I'm%20on%20Zoom%20or%20in%20front%20of%20the%20computer%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20time%2C%20which%20exposes%20me%20to%20a%20lot%20of%20artificial%20light.%20This%20light%20sparks%20different%20chemicals%20in%20our%20bodies%20that%20keep%20us%20up%20at%20night.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Ftreatments%2Fdo-blue-light-glasses-work%5C%22%3Eblue%20light%20blockers%3C%2Fa%3E%20block%20out%20that%20junk%20light%20so%20that%20my%20natural%20circadian%20rhythm%20isn't%20activated%20or%20thrown%20off.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E4.%20I%20stop%20drinking%20water%20at%205%20p.m.%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20an%20unbreakable%20rule.%20I%20always%20have%20a%20glass%20of%20water%20by%20my%20bed%2C%20in%20case%20I%20wake%20up%20parched%2C%20especially%20when%20I'm%20traveling.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20make%20sure%20to%20drink%20my%20gallon%20of%20water%20early%20%E2%80%94%20I'll%20drink%20up%20to%20about%20a%20gallon%20and%20a%20half%20per%20day.%C2%A0%20On%20nights%20when%20I%20don't%20have%20to%20get%20up%20to%20pee%2C%20I'm%20able%20to%20sleep%20deeper%20and%20stay%20in%20REM%20sleep%20because%20my%20body%20isn't%20triggering%20a%20signal%20that%20I%20need%20to%20go%20to%20the%20restroom.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E5.%20I%20avoid%20caffeine%20after%203%20p.m.%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20was%20living%20in%20Europe%2C%20I%20had%20a%20barista%20that%20would%20bring%20me%20espressos%20every%20day.%20However%2C%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fbest-time-of-day-to-drink-coffee-without-impacting-sleep-2018-10%5C%22%3Eeliminating%20that%20caffeine%20intake%20after%203%20p.m.%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I%20found%20that%20I%20was%20able%20to%20slow%20down%20and%20improve%20my%20quality%20of%20sleep%20through%20more%20rest%20and%20recovery.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20try%20to%20follow%20this%20in%20order%20to%20be%20at%20my%20best%2C%20but%20if%20I%20need%20to%20pull%20an%20all-nighter%20or%20jump%20online%20with%20the%20development%20team%2C%20then%20I'll%20drink%20coffee.%20There's%20a%20level%20of%20flexibility%20and%20forgiveness%20with%20it.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E6.%20I%20set%20the%20room%20temperature%20to%2065%20degrees%20Fahrenheit%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20need%20a%20lower%20resting%20heart%20rate%20to%20get%20into%20those%20deep%20levels%20of%20sleep%2C%20and%20cooler%20temperatures%20are%20one%20way%20to%20get%20there.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20temperature-controlled%20bedroom%20is%20always%20at%2065%20degrees%20Fahrenheit%2C%20which%20is%20the%20optimal%20temperature%20to%20maintain%20the%20body's%20core%20temperature.%20Even%20when%20I'm%20staying%20in%20a%20hotel%2C%20the%20first%20thing%20I'll%20do%20when%20I%20walk%20in%20is%20set%20the%20air%20conditioning%20to%2065%20degrees.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E7.%20I%20use%20a%20bed%20cooling%20device%20to%20keep%20body%20temp%20low%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20have%20a%20pad%20that%20I%20put%20over%20my%20bed.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Ftreatments%2Fhow-to-stay-cool-at-night%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIt%20cools%20my%20bed%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20the%20cold%20water%20running%20through%20it%2C%20and%20I%20can%20set%20the%20temperature%20to%20what%20I%20want%20it%20to%20be.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20also%20have%20a%20weighted%20blanket%20that%20has%20cold%20water%20flowing%20through%20it%20for%20the%20same%20purpose.%20The%20combination%20of%20the%20blanket%20with%2065%20degrees%20in%20the%20room%2C%20my%20cooling%20pad%2C%20ice%20bath%2C%20and%20other%20cooling%20devices%20is%20how%20I%20started%20hacking%20sleep%20and%20benefiting%20from%20my%20bedroom%20being%20a%20recovery%20hub.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E8.%20I%20try%20not%20to%20have%20any%20devices%20in%20the%20bedroom%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20don't%20bring%20my%20phone%20or%20other%20devices%20into%20my%20bedroom.%20I%20plug%20them%20into%20their%20charging%20stations%20in%20the%20living%20room%20for%20silence%20and%20darkness.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20I'm%20in%20a%20hotel%2C%20I'll%20unplug%20the%20coffee%20maker%2C%20TV%2C%20and%20the%20clock%20to%20create%20that%20dark%20environment.%20Darkness%20stimulates%20the%20production%20of%20melatonin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20home%2C%20I'll%20also%20turn%20off%20the%20WiFi%20at%20night%20so%20that%20I%20can%20create%20a%20space%20where%20there's%20no%20blue%20light%2C%20technology%2C%20or%20electromagnetic%20fields.%20If%20I%20open%20my%20eyes%20at%20night%2C%20nothing%20is%20going%20to%20trigger%20me%20and%20evoke%20the%20chemicals%20that%20keep%20me%20up.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E9.%20I%20use%20blackout%20curtains%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fwhy-youre-waking-up-in-middle-of-night-2019-3%5C%22%3EDarkness%20makes%20us%20feel%20more%20relaxed%3C%2Fa%3E%20which%20helps%20us%20fall%20asleep%20quicker%20and%20blackout%20curtains%20create%20that%20optimal%20dark%20environment.%20If%20I%20wanted%20to%20leverage%20a%20recharge%20nap%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20the%20day%2C%20the%20blackout%20curtains%20let%20me%20do%20so%20regardless%20of%20the%20time%20zone%20or%20hour.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E10.%20I%20solely%20focus%20on%20the%20optimization%20of%20sleep%2C%20not%20the%20length%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20perfect%20night%20of%20sleep%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Frem-sleep%5C%22%3Etwo%20hours%20of%20REM%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20two%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Ftreatments%2Fhow-to-get-more-deep-sleep%5C%22%3Ehours%20of%20deep%20sleep%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Some%20people%20need%20nine%20hours%20of%20sleep%20to%20achieve%20that.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20about%20the%20duration%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.healthline.com%2Fhealth%2Fhow-much-deep-sleep-do-you-need%23deep-sleep%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20goal%20is%20to%20achieve%20this%20ratio%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I've%20mastered%20my%20sleep%20to%20get%20my%202%3A2%20in%20six%20hours%2C%20all%20because%20I%20can%20get%20into%20those%20deeper%20zones%20faster%20with%20the%20environment%20that%20I've%20created.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E11.%20I%20monitor%20my%20sleep%20behavior%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20an%20AI%20data%20guy.%20I've%20tried%20every%20device%20on%20the%20market%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foura-smart-ring-review-why-wont-solve-back-to-work-2021-9%5C%22%3EOura%20ring%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20worked%20best%20for%20me.%20It's%20noninvasive%20and%20not%20bulky.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20can%20wear%20it%20on%20my%20finger%2C%20and%20it%20shows%20me%20the%20exact%20data%20I%20need%20to%20know%20about%20my%20REM%2C%20my%20deep%20sleep%2C%20my%20light%20sleep%2C%20and%20also%20my%20heart%20rate%2C.%20That's%20how%20I%20understand%20the%20nuances%20of%20what%20I%20do%20each%20day.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20data%20from%20this%20one%20device%20far%20outweighs%20any%20electrical%20signal%20the%20ring%20gives%20off%2C%20so%20I%20can%20constantly%20leverage%20this%20data%20to%20refine%20and%20refresh%20my%20sleeping.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EI'm%20at%20a%20point%20where%20I%20don't%20need%20an%20alarm%20to%20wake%20up%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20optimized%20my%20sleep%20so%20much%20that%20I%20wake%20up%20naturally%20once%20my%20body%20dictates%20that%20it's%20fully%20recovered%2C%20which%20is%20usually%20around%203%3A45%20a.m.%20I%20feel%20less%20rushed%2C%20more%20motivated%2C%20and%20in%20a%20better%20mood.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20invest%20in%20my%20sleep%2C%20my%20output%20is%20unrivaled.%20Sure%2C%20it's%20a%20commitment%20to%20understand%20the%20value%20of%20sleep%2C%20but%20it's%20worth%20investing%20in.%20Without%20that%20investment%2C%20we%20won't%20be%20as%20effective%20during%20the%20time%20that%20we're%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsleep-hacks-to-optimize-business-performance-2023-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689508500000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64b1e29bf9a2590019477015%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsleep-hacks-to-optimize-business-performance-2023-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Michael%20Koch%2C%20CEO%20of%20HubKonnect%20said%20he's%20mastered%20getting%20the%20perfect%20night's%20rest%20in%20six%20hours%20because%20of%20the%20sleep%20environment%20that%20he's%20created.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Robin%20Madel