was%20filming%20fake%20fight%20scenes%2C%20it%20is%20disgraceful%20that%20they%20and%20so%20many%20other%20journalists%20advanced%20his%20lies%20for%20so%20long.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20acts%20of%20media%20malpractice%20not%20only%20gaslit%20me%20and%20many%20others%2C%20they%20helped%20feed%20the%20Russian%20propaganda%20machine%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20continued.%20%26quot%3BLuckily%2C%20fundraising%20for%20charities%20focused%20on%20the%20Armed%20Forces%20of%20Ukraine%20has%20been%20able%20to%20emerge%20unscathed%20from%20this%20debacle%20as%20have%20the%20reputations%20of%20every%20real%20foreign%20soldier.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EGuns%2C%20money%2C%20and%20battalions%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EVasquez%20frequently%20posted%20images%20of%20weapons%2C%20including%20American%20guns%2C%20that%20he%20said%20he%20had%20been%20given%2C%20but%20it%20is%20unclear%20where%20he%20obtained%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20did%20not%20have%20a%20contract%20with%20the%20Ukrainian%20army%20or%20the%20International%20Legion%20so%20he%20wouldn't%20have%20been%20provided%20with%20weapons%20from%20any%20official%20authorities.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20asked%20by%20The%20New%20York%20Times%20in%20March%20where%20he%20got%20the%20guns%2C%20he%20responded%3A%20%26quot%3BI'm%20not%20exactly%20sure%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20added%20that%20they%20were%20%26quot%3Bbrand-new%2C%20out%20of%20the%20box%2C%20and%20we%20have%20plenty.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20sources%20told%20Insider%20that%20Vasquez%20had%20boasted%20about%20getting%20weapons%20on%20the%20black%20market.%20Insider%20was%20unable%20to%20verify%20those%20claims.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E(He%20once%20told%20a%20local%20Connecticut%20newspaper%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehour.com%2Fnews%2Farticle%2FNorwalk-veteran-says-he-s-heading-back-to-17254033.php%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Hour%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20want%20anything%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20and%20you%20got%20money%20and%20you%20know%20a%20couple%20of%20people%2C%20you%20can%20get%20it.%26quot%3B)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Two%20photographs%20of%20guns%20shared%20by%20James%20Vasquez%20on%20Twitter.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64aeb30d8ed31300199e9a7f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIt's%20unclear%20where%20Vasquez%20obtained%20weapons.%3Cp%3ETwitter%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20source%20of%20contention%20is%20how%20Vasquez%20used%20his%20platform%20to%20solicit%20donations%20from%20his%20followers%20to%20buy%20equipment%20for%20soldiers.%20Some%20of%20this%20money%20was%20raised%20for%20Ripley's%20Heroes%2C%20a%20US-based%20charity%20organization%20for%20which%20he%20was%20a%20prominent%20representative.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERipley's%20Heroes%20said%20it%20had%20raised%20over%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.kyivpost.com%2Fpost%2F16177%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20%241%20million%20over%20the%20past%20year%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20but%20the%20organization%20has%20faced%20questions%20about%20its%20spending%2C%20as%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F03%2F25%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Fvolunteers-us-ukraine-lies.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%20previously%20reported.%20As%20of%20March%2C%20some%20of%20the%20money%20appeared%20to%20have%20been%20spent%20on%20equipment%20that%20hadn't%20reached%20its%20intended%20destination.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVasquez%20often%20talked%20about%20fighting%20with%20various%20units%20%E2%80%94%20at%20one%20point%2C%20he%20said%20he%20was%20with%20a%20%26quot%3Bspecial%20forces%20unit%26quot%3B%20and%20later%20said%20he%20was%20fighting%20with%20the%20Da%20Vinci%20Wolves%20battalion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJohn%2C%20not%20his%20real%20name%2C%20an%20American%20man%20who's%20part%20of%20a%20group%20fighting%20in%20Ukraine%20called%20the%2013th%20group%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2F13thGroupUA%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWolverines%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20told%20Insider%20under%20the%20condition%20of%20anonymity%20that%20Vasquez%20likely%20overstated%20his%20relationship%20with%20the%20battalion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221400%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Two%20tweets%20from%20James%20Vasquez%20about%20the%20death%20of%20Da%20Vinci%2C%20leader%20of%20the%20Da%20Vinci%20Wolves%20battalion%2C%20and%20a%20video%20thumbnail%20of%20him%20attending%20the%20funeral.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64aeb3cc94be880019f392a9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221800%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EVasquez%20claimed%20he%20was%20part%20of%20the%20Da%20Vinci%20Wolves%20battalion.%3Cp%3ETwitter%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EJohn%2C%20who%20has%20been%20in%20Ukraine%20since%20the%20wider%20conflict%20with%20Russia%20began%20in%202014%2C%20said%20that%20he%20had%20been%20friendly%20with%20Da%20Vinci%20for%20some%20time.%20He%20told%20Insider%20that%20he%20saw%20Vasquez%20at%20the%20young%20battalion%20commander's%20funeral%2C%20which%20was%20attended%20by%20many%2C%20including%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fzelenskyy-attends-funeral-27-year-old-commander-da-vinci-2023-3%5C%22%3EPresident%20Volodymyr%20Zelenskyy.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJohn%20said%20that%20Vasquez%2C%20who%20was%20wearing%20a%20Da%20Vinci%20Wolves%20patch%20on%20his%20uniform%2C%20stuck%20out%20like%20a%20sore%20thumb%3A%20He%20didn't%20mingle%20with%20the%20other%20attendees%20but%20instead%20filmed%20himself%20for%20a%20video%20that%20was%20later%20posted%20on%20social%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEverybody's%20kneeling%2C%20their%20hands%20over%20their%20hearts%2C%20you%20know%2C%20to%20show%20respect%20and%20solidarity%20with%20each%20other%20in%20grief%20...%20and%20James%20is%20up%20there%20just%20filming%2C%26quot%3B%20John%20said.%20%26quot%3BAll%20these%20guys%20from%20Da%20Vinci's%20team%20are%20around%20and%20they're%20wearing%20the%20same%20patch%20right%2C%20but%20nobody%20recognizes%20him.%20Nobody%20comes%20up%20and%20says%20hi.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Wolves%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20Insider's%20request%20for%20comment.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20source%20linked%20to%20the%20Ukrainian%20army%2C%20speaking%20on%20the%20condition%20of%20anonymity%2C%20told%20Insider%20that%20Vasquez%20had%20returned%20to%20Ukraine%20as%20of%20early%20June.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20National%20Police%20in%20conjunction%20with%20the%20SBU%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20the%20Security%20Service%20of%20Ukraine%20%E2%80%94%20%26quot%3Bhas%20launched%20an%20investigation%20into%20both%20his%20possession%20of%20illegal%20weapons%20and%20his%20illicit%20fundraising%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20source%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E'James'%20visibility%20was%20great%2C%20until%20it%20wasn't%20anymore'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20many%20foreign%20fighters%2C%20joining%20the%20war%20can%20be%20a%20chance%20to%20reinvent%2C%20redeem%2C%20or%20prove%20themselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20see%2C%20over%20and%20over%20again%2C%20these%20broken%20people%20that%20showed%20up%20at%20the%20war.%20And%20they%20saw%20it%20from%20day%20one%20as%20an%20opportunity%20to%20have%20a%20new%20life%20to%20become%20a%20social-media%20hero%2C%20whatever%20you%20want%20to%20call%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Tim%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20had%20my%20own%20things%20to%20gain%20by%20going%20to%20Ukraine%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20not%20blameless.%20I%20have%20one%20leg%3B%20it's%20a%20recent%20amputation.%20And%20one%20of%20the%20reasons%20that%20I%20went%20was%20to%20feel%20like%20a%20whole%20human%20being%20again%20by%20helping%20other%20people.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMalcolm%20Nance%2C%20a%20former%20MSNBC%20analyst%20who%20is%20now%20part%20of%20Ukraine's%20International%20Legion%2C%20was%20the%20only%20prominent%20foreign%20fighter%20to%20defend%20Vasquez%20after%20his%20falsehoods%20were%20revealed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BJames%20was%20NOT%20fake%2C%20he%20was%20troubled.%20He%20did%20a%20lot%20for%20Ukraine%20but%20has%20challenges%20to%20face.%20Respect%20what%20he%20did%20do%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote%20on%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FMalcolmNance%2Fstatus%2F1638602411441790981%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETwitter%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20described%20Vasquez%20as%20%26quot%3Ba%20soldier%20in%20need%20of%20care%20on%20several%20levels%26quot%3B%20and%20criticized%20those%20who%20spoke%20out%20against%20him.%20Nance%20declined%20to%20speak%20with%20Insider%20on%20the%20record.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20the%20debate%20is%20whether%20Vasquez%20did%20any%20good%20in%20Ukraine%20despite%20his%20lies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20sources%20told%20Insider%20that%20Vasquez%20did%20not%20help%20in%20terms%20of%20front-line%20fighting%2C%20his%20social-media%20presence%20did%20have%20a%20positive%20effect%20%E2%80%94%20at%20least%20for%20a%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BJames%20certainly%20helped%20with%20morale%2C%26quot%3B%20Tim%20said.%20%26quot%3BJames%20certainly%20helped%20with%20public%20relations.%20He%20did%2C%20inadvertently%2C%20a%20lot%20of%20good.%20James'%20visibility%20was%20great%2C%20until%20it%20wasn't%20anymore.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerican-social-media-war-hero-accused-stolen-valor-in-ukraine-2023-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689503557000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64aead4594be880019f390de%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.