%20hijacked%20from%20the%20cradle%2C%20but%20some%20turtles%20will%20make%20it%20to%20the%20sea.%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cem%3E%E2%88%BC%20Wayne%20Shorter%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20guess%20you%20can%20blame%20Wayne%20Shorter%20for%20making%20legions%20of%20rock-and-roll%20fans%20believe%20they%20were%20actually%20listening%20to%20jazz%2C%20when%20he%20took%20a%20solo%20on%20Steely%20Dan%E2%80%99s%20tune%20Aja%2C%20back%20in%201977.%20But%20this%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20because%20of%20some%20deeply%20thought-out%20decision%20by%20Shorter%2C%20to%20misappropriate%20the%20ears%20of%20rock-and-rollers.%20The%20truth%20is%20rather%20banal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnewmusicusa.org%2Fnmbx%2Fnotes-from-the-custerdome-a-jazz-appreciation-of-steely-dan%2F%5C%22%3Einterview%20by%20Eugene%20Holley%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20in%20NewMusicUsa.org%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20had%20this%20piece%20(%E2%80%98Aja%E2%80%99)%2C%20which%20had%20this%20long%20modal%20section%2C%E2%80%9D%20Fagen%20(%3Cem%3EDonald%2C%20co-founder%20of%20Steely%20Dan%3C%2Fem%3E)%20proudly%20told%20me%20in%20my%20interview%20with%20him%20in%202013.%C2%A0%20%E2%80%9CAnd%20we%20thought%2C%20%E2%80%98who%20would%20be%20the%20ideal%20person%20for%20the%20track%3F%E2%80%99%20And%20we%20said%2C%20%E2%80%98Wayne%20Shorter.%E2%80%99%20On%20the%20first%20try%2C%20he%20said%20no.%20But%20we%20knew%20someone%20who%20knew%20him%2C%20and%20he%20asked%20him%2C%20because%20he%20didn%E2%80%99t%20know%20who%20we%20were.%20So%20we%20sent%20him%20the%20track%2C%20and%20he%20liked%20it%20and%20decided%20to%20come%20in.%20And%20he%20nailed%20it%20on%20the%20first%20take.%20That%20was%20one%20of%20the%20best%20moments%20for%20us.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMusicians%2C%20like%20other%20professionals%2C%20are%20for%20hire.%20And%20sometimes%20they%20change%20the%20course%20of%20history%20without%20meaning%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWayne%20Shorter%20significantly%20influenced%20the%20way%20jazz%20bifurcated%20from%20bebop%2C%20a%20complex%20and%20virtuosic%20form%20of%20music%20dominating%20the%20scene%20in%20the%20late%20%E2%80%9950s%20and%20%E2%80%9960s%2C%20to%20the%20more%20accessible%20jazz%20fusion%20of%20the%20%E2%80%9970s.%20Not%20merely%20as%20a%20sax-for-hire%20with%20Steely%20Dan%20or%20Joni%20Mitchell%2C%20but%20in%20a%20deliberate%20and%20conscious%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20part%20of%20a%20movement%20that%20was%20taking%20place%20in%20New%20York%20City%20which%20began%20with%20Miles%20Davis.%20Davis%20was%20at%20the%20time%20the%20most%20significant%20and%20influential%20jazz%20musician%20in%20the%20whole%20world.%20If%20you%20got%20a%20gig%20playing%20with%20Miles%2C%20your%20career%20was%20pretty%20much%20made.%20Shorter%E2%80%99s%20biographer%20Michelle%20Mercer%20recalls%20what%20he%20said%20about%20the%20first%20time%20he%20played%20on%20stage%20with%20Davis.%20%E2%80%9CI%20felt%20like%20a%20cello%2C%20I%20felt%20the%20viola%2C%20I%20felt%20liquid%2C%20dot-dash%2C%20and%20colours%20started%20really%20coming.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShorter%20played%20in%20his%20band%20from%20the%20mid%20%E2%80%9960s%20to%20the%20early%20%E2%80%9970s.%20Davis%20was%20focused%20on%20reaching%20out%20to%20the%20enormous%20audiences%20generously%20funding%20the%20rock%2C%20folk%20and%20funk%20steamroller%20of%20the%20day.%20His%20way%20was%20to%20create%20a%20simpler%2C%20groove%20based%2C%20swayable%20type%20of%20music%20with%20way%20fewer%20chord%20changes.%20It%20naturally%20allowed%20the%20inclusion%20of%20many%20more%20fans%20who%20easily%20found%20relatable%20moments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20404px)%2085vw%2C%20404px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F16142635%2FWayne-Shorter_in_Amsterdam_1980.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22404%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F16142635%2FWayne-Shorter_in_Amsterdam_1980.jpeg%20647w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F16142635%2FWayne-Shorter_in_Amsterdam_1980-190x300.jpeg%20190w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-663444%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22639%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EWayne%20Shorter%20playing%20with%20Weather%20Report%2C%20Amsterdam%2C%201980.%20Photo%3A%20Chris%20Hakkens%2FCC%20BY%202.0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20time%20Miles%E2%80%99%20Bitches%20Brew%20was%20released%2C%20it%20was%20just%20a%20matter%20of%20time%20before%20the%20stellar%20band%20members%20all%20branched%20out%20on%20their%20own%20creating%20a%20powerful%20jazz%20fusion%20age.%20The%20most%20famous%20of%20them%20were%20John%20McLaughlin%20(Mahavishnu%20Orchestra)%2C%20Chick%20Corea%20(Return%20to%20Forever)%2C%20Wayne%20Shorter%20and%20Joe%20Zawinul%20(Weather%20Report).%20There%20were%20many%20others%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShorter%20came%20from%20a%20solid%20bebop%20background%20and%20you%20can%20hear%20this%20in%20his%20phrasing%2C%20even%20during%20the%20Weather%20Report%20era.%20But%20he%20wanted%20to%20shed%20that%20persona%20and%20believe%20in%20what%20he%20was%20trying%20to%20create.%20%E2%80%9CI%E2%80%99m%20not%20into%20composition.%20I%E2%80%99m%20into%20decomposition%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20once%20told%20musician%20Jason%20Moran.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20a%20lyrical%20and%20vocal%20quality%20to%20his%20soloing%2C%20which%20is%20perhaps%20why%20through%20his%20career%20he%20has%20collaborated%20with%20vocalists.%20Something%20that%20makes%20my%20heart%20sing.%20I%20loved%20his%20album%20Native%20Dancer%20with%20Milton%20Nascimento%20released%20in%201975.%20%E2%80%9CYou%20know%20the%20kind%20of%20bossa%20nova%20that%20sells%3F%20%E2%80%98Girl%20From%20Ipanema%E2%80%99%20that%20kind%20of%20thing%3F%20Well%2C%20that%E2%80%99s%20ok%E2%80%A6%20but%20he%20(%3Cem%3ENascimento%3C%2Fem%3E)%20was%20coming%20from%20the%20underpinnings%20of%20molte-something%2C%20the%20Amazon%20and%20Africa%20and%20everything%2C%20and%E2%80%A6%20he%20had%20another%20sound%20in%20his%20voice.%20It%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20like%20he%20was%20trying%20to%20be%20someone%20else%2C%E2%80%9D%20Shorter%20told%20Christian%20McBride%20in%20an%20interview.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20mid%201970s%20is%20when%20I%20moved%20to%20New%20York%20City%20and%20took%20my%20own%20stab%20at%20the%20jazz%20scene%20there.%20I%20was%20playing%20with%20Ryo%20Kawasaki%2C%20a%20Japanese%20jazz%20guitar%20player%20with%20amazing%20chops%20and%20a%20lovely%20sense%20of%20where%20music%20was%20headed.%20We%20made%20a%20couple%20of%20albums%20together.%20He%20was%20also%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Gil%20Evans%20Orchestra%20and%20Elvin%20Jones%E2%80%99%20band.%20One%20day%20he%20told%20me%20that%20Wayne%20Shorter%20and%20Weather%20Report%20were%20looking%20for%20a%20singer%20and%20that%20he%20had%20sent%20them%20some%20music%20that%20we%20had%20recorded%20together.%20I%20was%20kind%20of%20taken%20aback%20and%20mostly%20started%20to%20panic.%20I%20had%20no%20idea%20if%20I%20could%20do%20it%20and%20really%20didn%E2%80%99t%20like%20the%20idea%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20my%20huge%20surprise%20Shorter%20called%20me%20one%20afternoon%2C%20probably%20around%201978%20or%201979%2C%20and%20we%20talked%20for%20a%20while%20on%20the%20phone.%20He%20said%20he%20really%20liked%20my%20singing%20and%20was%20considering%20a%20vocalist%20for%20the%20band.%20Nothing%20happened%20after%20that%20and%20I%E2%80%99m%20glad%2C%20because%20I%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20ready%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201993%20my%20friend%2C%20jazz%20vocalist%20and%20fellow%20Ryo%20Kawasaki%20alumnus%20Clare%20Forster%2C%20made%20an%20entire%20album%20of%20his%20music%20called%2C%20%E2%80%98Clare%20Forster%20Sings%20Wayne%20Shorter.%E2%80%99%20It%E2%80%99s%20a%20beautiful%20tribute%20to%20him%20and%20the%20singing%20is%20just%20magnificent.%20She%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CFor%20many%20years%20I%20have%20been%20a%20great%20admirer%20of%20Wayne%20Shorter%E2%80%99s%20compositions.%20His%20raw%2C%20human%20sound%20through%20the%20saxophone%20first%20drew%20me%20to%20his%20music.%E2%80%9D%20Perhaps%20deliberately%2C%20she%20leaves%20out%20Footprints%2C%20Shorter%E2%80%99s%20most%20famous%20tune%20and%20one%20that%20has%20been%20widely%20covered%20by%20many%20musicians.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECut%20to%202021%20and%20Wayne%20Shorter%2C%20age%2088%20has%20collaborated%20with%20the%20Harvard%20professor%2C%20Grammy-winning%2C%20bass%20player%20and%20vocalist%20Esperanza%20Spalding%20to%20produce%20an%20enormous%20piece%20of%20work%20named%20Ephigenia.%20It%E2%80%99s%20an%20opera%20that%20took%20eight%20years%20to%20make%20and%20involved%20all%20sorts%20of%20obstacles%20and%20challenges.%20Luckily%2C%20they%20were%20able%20to%20stage%20multiple%20performances%20before%20Wayne%20Shorter%20took%20his%20final%20encore%2C%20saying%20to%20the%20audience%2C%20%E2%80%9CNothing%20is%20what%20I%E2%80%99m%20try%20to%20keep%20and%20go%20forward%20with.%20Nothing.%20Thank%20you.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERIP%20Wayne.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.radhathomas.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERadha%20Thomas%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20jazz%20vocalist%2C%20composer%20and%20author.%20She%20lives%20in%20Bangalore%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689497920000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F16142752%2F2801307405_36e6652c07_k.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fculture%2Fsaxophonist-wayne-shorter-changed-history-sometimes-consciously-sometimes-not%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Wayne%20Shorter%20significantly%20influenced%20the%20way%20jazz%20bifurcated%20from%20bebop%2C%20a%20complex%20and%20virtuosic%20form%20of%20music%20dominating%20the%20scene%20in%20the%20late%20'50s%20and%20'60s%2C%20to%20the%20m